 <h2><U>Instaclick Eye of Zomm</U></h2></center><br><br>Unfortunately, this guide is only of any use to mages. "Wait!" I hear you cry, "Mages already have that spell, right?". Yes, yes we do. But that does NOT make this item worthless. And no, I'm not concerned about the mana this level8 spell uses.<br><br>How much do you use this spell? (Or its older brother: Eye of Tallon). I bet you don't use it much, but it can be very useful. The reason you don't use it, is the effort involved in losing a valuable spell, sitting down and finding eye of zomm, using it, replacing it when done... A lot of effort right? Not to mention sometimes impossible or at least dangerous for the sitting or even spell dropping required. But wait! There is an easier way.<br><br>How about just right clicking an item in your inventory? Sound easier? It takes no mana, no effort, no changing of spells. This means that whenever you want to see whats around the corner, where the tank has got to, if that mob is up... just click. It can be amazingly useful when its an instaclick, a spell you never used before can be rediscovered.<br><br><br>And mages are lucky. There are several items that insta-proc eye of zomm, but we get the only one with unlimited charges!<br><img src="http://www.rpgexpert.com/zomm/claybracelet.gif"><br><br>Ok. I have hopefully convinced you that this toy is a nice little item to own, now to get you one.<br><br><b><u>Getting the Bracelet</u></b><br><br>OK, you need four quest items named "A Rune of Clay", all identicle, but they all identify differently.<br><br>First stop: The Rathe Mountains. You will be hunting level25 gnomish necros, and can get two at a time with some skeletons, so make sure you can handle it or have help. The gnomes we're looking for are these three:<br><img src="http://www.rpgexpert.com/zomm/gnomes.JPG"><br><br><a href="http://eqbeastiary.allakhazam.com/search.shtml?id=3076">Bindlegrob</a>, <a href="http://eqbeastiary.allakhazam.com/search.shtml?id=3079">Sindlerob</a> and <a href="http://eqbeastiary.allakhazam.com/search.shtml?id=3078">Findlegrob</a>, found in the following places in Rathe Mountains:<br><img src="http://www.rpgexpert.com/zomm/rathegnm.jpg"><br><br>Smoke them out and kill them, more than once if you need to, until you have a rune off each. (6 min spawn time if it doesn't drop first try).<br><br>Now your almost there, all you need to do now is find and kill <a href="http://eqbeastiary.allakhazam.com/search.shtml?id=2556">this fella</a> in the Ocean of Tears:<br><img src="http://www.rpgexpert.com/zomm/goblinhm.jpg"><br><br>Look for loc neg1200, neg8560, and you will either find him or a placeholder to kill. He will eventually drop the fourth rune. All you have to do now, is head over to the <a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/zones/Antonica/Solusek_Ro.htm">Temple of Soulsek Ro</a> and hand them into <a href="http://eqbeastiary.allakhazam.com/search.shtml?id=3288">Joyce</a>. Enjoy your new toy!<br><br><br><br></center><b><u>Zone Information:</u></b><br><br><a href='http://www.eqmages.com' onClick='moblist(10); return false;'>Temple of Soulsek Ro mob list</a><br>
<a href='http://www.eqmages.com' onClick='questlist(10); return false;'>Temple of Soulsek Ro quest list</a><br><a href='http://www.eqatlas.com/templesro.html'>Temple of Soulsek Ro Map</a><br><br><b><u>Comments/Feedback:</u></b><br><br><i><b>Eandori Raintree</b> says:</i><br>I always knew of this item, but never bothered to go get it.  I just did this quest from start to finish by myself within an hour.  Very easy, all the mobs were up, so I just used Plane of Knowledge books to go to Ogguk then ran to Rathe Mountains for 3 Runes, then gated back to PoK, zoned to Freeport, rode the boat to Ocean of Tears, killed the Goblin on the island near the Oracle, gated to PoK again, zoned to Neriak book, ran to Temple of Sol Ro and got my item.  Then I zoned into Solusek B and solo'd all over testing it out.  It's very nice indeed, wish I had gotten it years before.  I like sending in a buffed pet to fight, then clicking the bracer from inventory and sitting.  So while I'm medding, and pet is fighting, I'm scouting all over the place.<br><br><i><b>Anonymous</b> says:</i><br>not sure you can use an eye while you have a pet...is handy if you have suspend minion if thats so<br><br><i><b>Anonymous</b> says:</i><br>You can use the eye with a pet. The eye is a spell effect not a pet.<br><br><i><b>Eandori Raintree</b> says:</i><br>Yes you can cast the Eye of Zomm with a pet up and not lose the pet.  No you cannot cast Eye of Tallon with a pet up and not lose the pet.  This is because Eye of Tallon casts invis on you when it pops, and the invis kills the pet.<br><br><i><b>aristot</b> says:</i><br>Was in Veskar the other day with fellow guildie and mage Zzarenth.  Can't exactly remember how it happened but he died.  Anyhow i got a rezz for him, cleric zones in and tells me ive never been in zone B4 how do i get to ya?? i use my trusty insta EOZ to find and target cleric, then COH him to corpse. <br><br><i><b>Mixolydian</b> says:</i><br>I regularly use the eye as a no aggro scout. (invaluable in LDoN!)It has to be one of the most underrated mage spells in the game.The fact that there is a clicky for it just made my day.:-)><br><br><i><b>Anonymous</b> says:</i><br>Hmm, why "only mages"? I see no reason I cannot do this quest as a non mage and simply click from my inventory.<br><br><i><b>Acideus 49th mage Tallon Zek</b> says:</i><br>how do you suspend minion?? and what is it lol? sorry for my stupidity but my mage is still low<br><br><i><b>Anonymous</b> says:</i><br>suspend minion is a pet command you can use after you get the AA Pet Disapline.  Hope this helps.<br><br><i><b>Anonymous</b> says:</i><br>No, no it's not, suspend minion is an ability you can use after you get the AA....suspend minion. It is not a command, and you do not get it from Pet Discipline.<br><br><form action='rate.php' method='post' name='rate'>
